13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 03:40:37";s:12:"post_content";s:1129:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>
<div><strong>Carol Pepper</strong> is the CEO¬†and Founder of Pepper International, an award-winning family office that has served global families with over $100 million in net worth since 2001.¬†Prior to forming her own firm, she managed assets for the Rockefeller Family Office, and was a top Private Banker at JP Morgan, Credit Suisse and Citibank Private Bank. Carol is the author of <em>The Seven Pearls of Financial Wisdom,</em> written with Camilla Webster, and <em>Beyond Blood, </em>a wealth management thriller.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Carol Pepper has been speaking professionally since 2001. She regularly speaks around the globe at financial wealth management conferences. Her message of financial clarity in an era of market confusion resonates with all types of audiences.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Carol is a graduate of Bryn Mawr College and has an MBA from Colombia Business School in Entrepreneurial Studies. She enjoys taking the mystery out of high finance and helping investors understand how to prosper in any market environment.</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Carol Pepper";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"carol-pepper";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-29 09:19:52";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-29 13:19:52";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=413";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:45;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"387";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:58:21";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:58:21";s:12:"post_content";s:1146:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>At the early stages of his career, Carson Morton was a professional musician playing with his band, Razmataz. He moved away from music and began his writing career as a playwright, publishing works in the United States and in Europe. Carson Morton is a screenwriter and published playwright, and has worked in television as a consultant and composer. His screenplay, <em>Finder‚Äôs Keepers</em>, won first prize in the 1998 Hollywood Film Festival Columbus Discovery Awards.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Stealing Mona Lisa is his first novel. Based on the actual theft of the Mona Lisa from the Louvre in 1911, Stealing Mona Lisa is a captivating action-packed historical mystery. The novel is a Kirkus Reviews Best of 2011 Mysteries title and one of Library Journal‚Äôs Best Mystery Books of 2011. Carson Morton has appeared on NPR‚Äôs WYSO Public Radio for the Miami Valley, was a panelist at the 2011 Southern Festival of Books and spoken at many book signings.</div>
<div></div>
<div>‚ÄúCarson Morton is, quite frankly, a masterful storyteller.‚Äù
‚ÄîNew York Journal of Books</div>
