<div>
<div>

Chandler Burr is The New York Times' perfume critic. His new book, <em>The Perfect Scent: A Year Inside the Perfume Industry in Paris &amp; New York</em>, tells two parallel stories, the first about a year Burr spent for The New Yorker magazine in Paris behind the scenes at Herm√®s watching legendary perfumer Jean-Claude Ellena create the Herm√®s scent "Un Jardin sur le Nil"; and the second about a year (beginning with an article for The New York Times) inside Coty with Sarah Jessica Parker as she directed the making of her perfume "Lovely."

His first novel, <em>You Or Someone Like You</em>, will be published¬†in the summer of 2009. It was originally excerpted as a novel in progress by narrativemagazine.com

Burr is also author of the books <em>The Emperor of Scent: A True Story of Perfume, Obsession, and the Last Mystery of the Senses</em> and <em>A Separate Creation: The Search for the Biological Origins of Sexual Orientation, </em>based on his Atlantic cover story, "Homosexuality and Biology."

He speaks around the world on scent and perfume and hosts interactive masterclasses in gourmand scents; this series explains perfume for the lay person and shows fragrance's structure and artistry, with food-based scent raw materials (absolutes of cinnamon, clove, pepper) and gourmand perfumes like "Angel" (which uses the scent of cotton candy) and "Shalimar" (the scent of vanilla) reflected in a 7-course gourmet meal.

Beginning his journalism career as a stringer at the Christian Science Monitor's Southeast Asia bureau in Manila, Burr then earned a Masters in International Economics &amp; Japan studies from the Paul H. Nitze School/Johns Hopkins. He has also studied international relations at l'Institut d'√©tudes politiques in Paris and Chinese history at Min Zu Xue Yuen (Central Institute of Foreign Nationalities) in Beijing.

Burr has written on business for Fast Company and Fortune, politics for the New York Times Magazine, on travel and food for Gourmet, Food &amp; Wine, Cond√© Nast Traveler, Travel + Leisure, and Departures, and religion and science for US News &amp; World Report, where he was a Contributing Editor. His first stage play, "Exquisite," was nominated in 1992 for the Helen Hayes award for Outstanding New Play.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Chandler Burr";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"chandler-burr";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 14:45:16";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 18:45:16";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=170";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:47;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"493";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 13:25:15";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 13:25:15";s:12:"post_content";s:4495:"<strong>Chantal Sicile-Kira</strong>‚Äôs¬†passion for empowering others, her love of writing, and her personal interest in autism has led her to become an award-winning author, speaker, and leader in the field of adolescence and transition to adulthood. She has been involved with autism spectrum disorders for over 20 years as both a parent and a professional on both sides of the Atlantic. Recently, Chantal founded Autism College in order to provide more information and online training to parents and educators. She has given over 125 talks in 21 different states and six countries.Born into a large French family, Chantal was brought up bilingual and bicultural in Ohio, New York and California. Family pastimes included cooking frog legs for breakfast over an open fire during summers spent camping in Louisville, Kentucky. Chantal received her BA in Social Ecology from the University of California at Irvine. Her first practical experience with autism was at Fairview State Hospital, teaching self-help and community living skills to severely developmentally disabled and autistic adolescents in preparation for their deinstitutionalization. Then, as a case manager for Orange County Regional Center for the Developmentally Disabled, Chantal provided information and resources to families.Little did Chantal know that years later, these work experiences would prove invaluable when her son Jeremy, now a young adult, was born and eventually diagnosed with autism in Paris, France, where the only treatment on offer was psychoanalysis. Chantal‚Äôs struggle to find appropriate treatment for her son led them to move to England, where they became one of the first families in the UK to run a Lovaas-type (based on applied behavior analysis) home program. Having been a service provider in California, and then a parent raising her child and dealing with the ‚Äôsystems‚Äô in France, United Kingdom and the United States, gives Chantal a unique and well-rounded perspective few people in this field have.In 2009 Chantal was appointed by the¬†California Senate Select Committee on Autism &amp; Related Disorders to Co-Chair the South Counties Autism Regional Taskforce. Chantal had previously served on the Taskforce on Transitional Services &amp; Supports reporting to the California Legislative Blue Ribbon Commission on Autism.A former researcher on BBC documentaries and a line producer on a TV Series in Paris, Chantal has written five books.¬†She writes for <em>The Huffington Post</em> and PyschologyToday.com. Chantal‚Äôs fifth book, co-authored with her son Jeremy, is called A<em> Full Life with Autism: From Learning to Forming Relationships to Achieving Independence</em>, and will be published in March 2012. Her fourth book, <em>41 Things to Know About Autism</em>, has been revised and published as <em>What is Autism?: Understanding Life with Autism or Asperger‚Äôs. </em>Chantal‚Äôs first book, <em>Autism Spectrum Disorders: The Complete Guide to Understanding Autism, Asperger‚Äôs Syndrome, Pervasive Developmental Disorder, and other ASD‚Äôs </em>was the recipient of the 2005 Autism Society of America‚Äôs Outstanding Literary Work of the Year Award, and was nominated for the 2005 PEN/Martha Albrand Award for First Nonfiction. The UK edition was the winner of the 2003 San Diego Book Award for ‚ÄòBest in Health.‚Äô Her second book, <em>Adolescents on the Autism Spectrum: A Parent‚Äôs Guide to the Cognitive, Social, Physical, and Transition Needs of Teenagers with Autism Spectrum Disorders</em>, was awarded the 2006 San Diego Book Award for ‚ÄòBest in Health/Fitness.‚ÄôChantal‚Äôs third book, <em>Autism Life Skills: From Communication and Safety to Self Esteem and More: 10 Essential Abilities Every Child Deserves and Needs to Learn</em> (foreword by Temple Grandin, PhD)¬†was published by Penguin (US) in October 2008, and Random House (UK) in May 2009.Jeremy, Chantal‚Äôs son, was¬†highlighted in the <em>Newsweek</em> cover story "Growing up with Autism‚Äô and featured in the MTV documentary <em>True Life</em> series, in "I Have Autism‚Äô which was the recipient of a 2008 Voice Award.¬†His commencement speech for Torrey Pines High School was covered by the media. Chantal‚Äôs experience of¬†raising her¬†son in France, the UK and California was the subject of a 22 page article in the French professional journal on education and research for special education, La Nouvelle Revue de l‚ÄôAdaptation et de la Scolarisation, June 2006, published by INS HEA.";s:10:"post_title";s:19:"Chantal Sicile-Kira";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:19:"chantal-sicile-kira";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 14:51:49";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 18:51:49";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=493";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:48;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"491";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 13:16:33";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 13:16:33";s:12:"post_content";s:808:"<strong>Charles J. Shields</strong> is the author of <em><a href="http://us.macmillan.com/andsoitgoes">And So It Goes: Kurt Vonnegut: A Life</a></em>, <em><a href="http://us.macmillan.com/mockingbird">Mockingbird: A Portrait of Harper Lee</a></em>, the highly acclaimed, bestselling biography of Harper Lee, and <em><a href="http://us.macmillan.com/iamscout">I Am Scout: The Biography of Harper Lee</a></em> (Henry Holt Books for Young Readers). He grew up in the Midwest and taught in a rural school in central Illinois for several years. He has been a reporter for public radio, a journalist, and the author of nonfiction books for young people. He and his wife live near Charlottesville, Virginia. Visit Charles J. Shields's website at <a href="http://www.CharlesJShields.com">www.CharlesJShields.com</a>.";s:10:"post_title";s:18:"Charles J. Shields";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:17:"charles-j-shields";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-29 16:16:26";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-29 20:16:26";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=491";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:49;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"168";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 14:05:25";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 14:05:25";s:12:"post_content";s:776:"herie Burns is the author of the biography, <em>Searching for Beauty‚ÄîThe Life of Millicent Roger,</em> published by St. Martin‚Äôs Press in September of 2011.¬† <em>The Santa Fe New Mexican</em> called the book ‚Äúa fast-paced, insightful romp.‚Äù Burns‚Äô previous books are <em>The Great Hurricane: 1938,</em> (published by Grove/Atlantic) and <em>Stepmotherhood‚ÄîHow to Survive Without Feeling Frustrated, Left Out or Wicked</em> (Times Books).¬† <em>Stepmotherhood</em> has sold over 40,000 copies in the U.S., England, and Germany and remains in print after twenty years. Her work has also appeared in <em>The New York Times Magazine, People, Glamour, New York, Sports Illustrated, Constitution</em> and other publications. She now lives primarily in Taos, New Mexico.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Cherie Burns";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"cherie-burns";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 14:54:43";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 18:54:43";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=168";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:50;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"394";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 03:14:55";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 03:14:55";s:12:"post_content";s:1975:"Emerging star on the lifestyle scene and <em>New York Times </em>bestselling author Cheryl Najafi encourages others to "break the rules of proper entertaining." Gone are the unattainable expectations of being the perfect host that make gatherings about as fun and stress-free as trying on swimsuits‚ÄîCheryl shows you how to relax, use what you already have, and be yourself. Cheryl shows you new ways to decorate using repurposed items from around the house, with unique twists that will wow guests the moment they arrive. From mixing and matching dishes to putting together an outfit from the basics already in your closet, her ideas are fresh and simple, and easy for anyone to put to good use.A down-home girl originally from rural Missouri, Cheryl‚Äôs whirlwind past two decades have been filled with entertaining distinguished guests from around the globe. Her ability to blend the everyday with the sophisticated can be seen in everything from her dinner table to her wardrobe. And it always leaves people wanting to know more.

An author, speaker, and CEO of leading lifestyle media company CherylStyle, Cheryl is first and foremost a mother, wife and friend who is there when you need her with style tips and tricks for your next great gathering. Having taught public speaking at the college level for five years, Cheryl has given numerous addresses to audiences of 200 to 2,500 people at university, community and charity functions. She has made opening remarks for Giada De Laurentiis at The Metropolitan Cooking &amp; Entertaining Show, served as a keynote speaker for the Snap Conference, a guest speaker for the National Charity League, and an emcee for the International Design Association award ceremony. Cheryl‚Äôs new book, <em>You‚Äôre So Invited: Panic Less, Play More, and Get Your Party On! </em>was released by St. Martin‚Äôs Press on May 29, 2012. She holds a master‚Äôs degree in communication and performance studies from Arizona State University.";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Cheryl Najafi";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"cheryl-najafi";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 14:59:15";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 18:59:15";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=394";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:51;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"979";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-05-02 17:46:11";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-02 17:46:11";s:12:"post_content";s:3015:"Chris Trimble has dedicated more than a decade to studying the challenge that vexes even the best-managed corporations: <i>how to execute an innovation initiative</i>, that is, how to turn breakthrough ideas into actual products, services, and improvements<i>.</i>

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

He is the author of the landmark book, <i>The Other Side of Innovation: Solving the Execution Challenge</i>, with Vijay Govindarajan, as well as their <i>New York Times </i>bestselling follow-up, <i>Reverse Innovation: Create Far From Home, Win Everywhere</i>‚Äîwhich applied their research to the challenge of innovating to drive growth in emerging markets, while bringing those innovations home. A true visionary in his field, Trimble serves on the faculties of both the Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth and the Dartmouth Center for Health Care Delivery Science‚Äîwhere he is immersed in a multi-year effort to apply his work to the specific challenge of innovation in health care delivery.

&nbsp;

Trimble is actively enjoying the payoff of his work in its real-world application‚Äîworking shoulder-to-shoulder with innovation leaders in top corporations including General Electric, IBM, Intel, Microsoft, The New York Times Company, Genencor, Corning, Thomson Reuters, eBay, Fidelity, Unilever, and many, many others. A highly sought-after speaker, he has been welcomed by audiences at both public forums such as the <i>BusinessWeek</i> CEO Forum, the Conference Board‚Äôs Innovation Conference, and the HSM Innovation Forum‚Äîas well as for membership groups and associations such as American Public Power Association, Construction Industry Roundtable, CUSO Financial Services, Institute of Management Studies, and more.

&nbsp;

Chris Trimble first broke into the forefront of executive consciousness with his 2005 book, <i>Ten Rules for Strategic Innovators‚Äîfrom Idea to Execution</i>, which was on <i>The Wall Street Journal</i>‚Äôs Top Ten Recommended Reading list alongside <i>Freakonomics</i>, <i>The Tipping Point</i>, and <i>Blink. </i>It was selected by <i>Strategy &amp; Business </i>magazine as the best strategy book of the year. Notable articles include ‚ÄúStop the Innovation Wars,‚Äù with Vijay Govindarajan, which won a McKinsey Award as one of the <i>Harvard Business Review</i>‚Äôs best articles of the year, as well as ‚ÄúHow GE is Disrupting Itself,‚Äù with Jeff Immelt and Vijay Govindarajan. Trimble‚Äôs work has also appeared in the <i>MIT Sloan Management Review</i>, <i>California Management Review</i>, <i>Fast Company</i> and <i>The Financial Times</i>.

&nbsp;

With a career that mixes rigorous academic research with hard-nosed practical experience, Trimble credits his interest in innovation within large organizations as stemming from early experience as a submarine officer in the United States Navy. Trimble holds an MBA degree with distinction from the Tuck School of Business, and a Bachelor of Science degree with highest distinction from the University of Virginia.";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Chris Trimble";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"chris-trimble";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-03 15:41:23";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-03 19:41:23";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://www.macmillanspeakers.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=979";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:52;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"402";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 03:26:52";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 03:26:52";s:12:"post_content";s:580:"CHRISTINE O'DONNELL¬†was a¬†candidate for U.S. Senate in Delaware, most recently in 2010 for the Senate seat vacated by Joe Biden.¬† She‚Äôs been dubbed the ‚ÄúTea Party Darling‚Äù, ‚ÄúTroublemaker‚Äù by <em>Time</em>¬†and a leader of the ‚ÄúSecond American Revolution‚Äù by the foreign press.¬† She has appeared and continues to appear on and in a wide variety of media outlets, from <em>Good Morning America</em> to <em>People</em>, <em>The</em> <em>Rush Limbaugh</em> <em>Show</em> to¬†<em>Hannity</em>¬†and maintains a robust national speaking schedule. She lives in Delaware.";s:10:"post_title";s:19:"Christine O'Donnell";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:18:"christine-odonnell";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 15:06:48";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 19:06:48";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=402";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:53;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"546";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-12-18 16:36:43";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-12-18 16:36:43";s:12:"post_content";s:827:"When Dr. Van Tilburg's mountain rescue beeper goes off, the call may take him racing up a mountain peak to rescue an injured hiker, scaling a rocky ledge to intubate a hiker who has fallen over a cliff, into a blizzard to search for missing skiers, or to a mountain airplane crash scene for body recovery with his team, Hood River Crag Rats, the oldest mountain rescue group in the nation. Christopher Van Tilburg, MD, is a wilderness medicine specialist and author of eight books including <em>Mountain Rescue Doctor</em>.¬† Dr. Van Tilburg serves as medical contributor to National Geographic Adventure, Editor of Wilderness Medicine, and Contributing Editor to Backcountry and Columbia Gorge Magazine. He has appeared on the CBS Morning Show, CNN, and Jeep World of Sports. He lives with his daughters in Hood River, Oregon.";s:10:"post_title";s:23:"Christopher Van Tilburg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:23:"christopher-van-tilburg";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 15:53:14";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 19:53:14";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=546";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:54;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"343";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 00:04:21";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 00:04:21";s:12:"post_content";s:673:"<div>While caring for her ill and aging former father-in-law for several years, Cindy Laverty discovered that compassionate caregiving was her true calling and formed The Care Company, a southern California-based home care provider.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Today, as a leading spokesperson for the industry, Ms. Laverty has expanded her commitment to helping caregivers help others, through her entertaining, educational and insightful advice driven radio show. Her warm, yet practical approach to the process of caregiving provides listeners with first step knowledge and resources they can use to manage their lives and those they care for more peacefully.</div>
&nbsp;";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Cindy Laverty";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"cindy-laverty";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-29 15:18:46";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-29 19:18:46";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=343";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:55;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"137";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-12 22:29:40";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-12 22:29:40";s:12:"post_content";s:1255:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>
<div>Colin Beavan is the author of <em>Operation Jedburgh: D-Day and America‚Äôs First Shadow War</em> and <em>Fingerprints: The Origins of Crime Detection and the Murder Case that Launched Forensic Science.¬† </em>His work has appeared in <em>The Atlantic Monthly</em>, <em>Esquire</em>, <em>Mens‚Äô Journal</em>, <em>Mens‚Äô Health</em>, <em>Glamour</em>, <em>Cosmopolitan</em>, and many other national magazines. His books have been translated into Italian, German, French, Spanish, Portuguese, Korean, Japanese, and Chinese. Beavan has appeared on NPR‚Äôs <em>All Things Considered</em>, <em>The Kojo Nnamdi Show</em>, <em>Talk of the Nation</em>, and many other nationally syndicated NPR and commercial radio shows.<em> </em></div>
<div></div>
<div>His new book, No Impact Man, chronicles one year living in New YOrk while having zero impact on the environment.¬† This hilarious, insightful, profound look at living a sustainable life in the 21st century is destined to be a classic for years to come.</div>
<div></div>
<div>He lives in New York City with his wife Michelle Conlin, the accomplished <em>BusinessWeek</em> writer and editor, and their daughter, Isabella.</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Colin Beavan";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"colin-beavan";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 16:13:47";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 20:13:47";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=137";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:56;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"378";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:43:55";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:43:55";s:12:"post_content";s:3869:"Colum McCann is the author of two collections of short stories and five novels, including "This Side of Brightness,""Dancer" and ‚ÄúZoli,‚Äù all of which were international best-sellers. His newest novel is ‚ÄúLet the Great World Spin.‚Äù His fiction has been published in 30 languages and has appeared in The New Yorker, The Atlantic Monthly, GQ, Paris Review, Bomb and other places. He has written for numerous publications including The Irish Times, Die Zeit, La Republicca, Paris Match, The New York Times, the Guardian and the Independent.
<div></div>
<div>In 2003 Colum was named Esquire magazine's "Writer of the Year." Other awards and honors include a Pushcart Prize, the Rooney Prize, the Hennessy Award for Irish Literature, the Irish Independent Hughes and Hughes/Sunday Independent Novel of the Year 2003, and the 2002 Ireland Fund of Monaco Princess Grace Memorial Literary Award.</div>
<div></div>
<div>His short film "Everything in this Country Must," directed by Gary McKendry, was nominated for an Academy Award Oscar in 2005.</div>
<div></div>
<div>In May 2009 Colum was inducted into Aosdana, the equivalent of the Irish Academy, one of Ireland‚Äôs highest literary honours.</div>
<div></div>
<div>In fall 2009, Colum will be awarded a French Chevalier des arts et lettres by the French government, making him one of a exclusive number of foreign artists recognised in France for their literary contributions: other recipients have included Paul Auster, Salman Rushdie and Julian Barnes.</div>
<div></div>
<div>In September 2009 Colum will be awarded the Deauville Festival of Cinema Literary Prize in Deauxville, France.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Colum was born in Dublin in 1965 and began his career as a journalist in The Irish Press. In the early 1980's he took a bicycle across North America and then worked as a wilderness guide in a program for juvenile delinquents in Texas. After a year and a half in Japan, he and his wife Allison moved to New York where they currently live with their three children, Isabella, John Michael and Christian.</div>
<div>Colum teaches in Hunter College in New York, in the Creative Writing program, with fellow novelists Peter Carey and Nathan Englander.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Colum‚Äôs fifth novel, "Let the Great World Spin‚Äù is scheduled for release in the U.S on June 23rd, 2009. An extract was published in the Paris Review in fall 2008, followed by another extract in Bomb magazine. The British and Irish release will be in August, while European publishers will quickly follow up ‚Äì in what amounts to an unprecedented international publication ‚Äì in September 2009.</div>
<div></div>
<div>The novel begins in August 1974 as a tightrope walker makes his way through the dawn light across the World Trade Center towers, stunning thousands of watchers below. Using the true story of Philippe Petit as a pull-through metaphor, McCann crafts a portrait of the city and a people. There‚Äôs Corrigan, a radical young Irish monk, who struggles with his own demons as he lives among the prostitutes in the burning Bronx. A group of mothers gather in a Park Avenue apartment to mourn the sons who died in Vietnam ‚Äì they soon discover how much divides them even in their grief. Further uptown, Tillie, a 38-year-old grandmother, turns tricks alongside her teenaged daughter, determined not only to take care of her ‚Äúbabies‚Äù but to prove her own worth.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Elegantly weaving together these and other seemingly disparate lives, McCann‚Äôs powerful allegory of 9/11 comes alive in the unforgettable voices of the city‚Äôs people, unexpectedly drawn together by hope, beauty, and the tightrope walker‚Äôs ‚Äúartistic crime of the century.‚Äù McCann‚Äôs most ambitious work to date, Let the Great World Spin has already been described as a triumphant American novel.</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Colum McCann";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"colum-mccann";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 16:20:53";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 20:20:53";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=378";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:57;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"372";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:30:27";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:30:27";s:12:"post_content";s:1130:"During her successful career in medicine, Eleanor ‚ÄúConnie‚Äù Mariano has racked up an impressive list of ‚Äúfirsts.‚Äù¬† Not only was she the first Filipino-American to become a Rear Admiral in the US Navy, she also was the first female director of the White House Medical Unit, as well as the first military woman to be appointed as the White House Physician.¬† Born in 1955 in the Philippines, Mariano moved to the United States with her family at the age of two.¬† She graduated cum laude from the University of California, San Diego, earning her undergraduate degree in biology.¬† After joining the US Navy in 1977, she earned her medical degree from the Uniformed Services University of Medicine in 1981.¬† She later reached the rank of Rear Admiral in the navy and from there rose to the position of White House physician, where she provided medical service for two sitting presidents, George H.W. Bush and Bill Clinton.¬† In 2001, she retired from the navy and joined the Mayo Clinic of Scottsdale, Arizona.¬† Since then, she has founded the Center for Executive Medicine, a concierge medical service in North Scottsdale.";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Connie Mariano";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"connie-mariano";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 16:58:48";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 20:58:48";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=372";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:58;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"376";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:38:55";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:38:55";s:12:"post_content";s:2105:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>
<div>

Cyndi Maxey, MA, CSP, specializes in presentations skills and communication that drives profitable performance.

Maxey Creative's presentations, seminars, and learning tools are designed to produce successful speaking and¬†fine tune communication during change, all the while creatively approaching workplace learning and leadership. Whether speaking to groups or encouraging them to speak, Cyndi is a master communicator and facilitator.

Cyndi practices what she preaches. As a Certified Speaking Professional (an extremely distinguished recognition)¬†she speaks on average 75-90 times a year, most often to healthcare, pharmaceutical, women's, consumer, foodservice, insurance, and technical audiences. She is author of over 75 published articles and five books. Her latest book, <em>SPEAK UP! A Woman‚Äôs Guide to Presenting Like a Pro</em>, focuses on power presentations and influence skills for women. Also with coauthor Kevin O'Connor, Cyndi wrote the top-selling field guide, <em>PRESENT LIKE A PRO</em>. Based on work with over 382 physicians, engineers, and technical professionals,¬†<em>PRESENT LIKE A PRO</em>¬†demystifies public and professional speaking, and has been called a "must-read" for both aspiring speakers as well as industry professionals.

Owner of Maxey Creative Inc. since 1989 and a graduate of Northwestern University‚Äôs School of Speech, Maxey¬†blends¬†interaction, facts and fun¬†to encourage learning and retention. Having acted in over 30 professional plays as well as many voice-overs and commercials, she brings a strong performance background to her coaching and presentations. She has also been¬†President of the National Speakers Association (Illinois Chapter) and a former Board member of three other associations. Maxey is a strong advocate for volunteerism and will encourage your volunteer leaders and trainers as well.

She lives in Chicago with an active family and a four-year old Labrador Retriever, Max Maxey, who provide both balance and chaos in her life.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:11:"Cyndi Maxey";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:11:"cyndi-maxey";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 17:01:04";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 21:01:04";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=376";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:59;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"339";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:59:05";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:59:05";s:12:"post_content";s:2178:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>
<div>

Toronto-born Daniel Lak was a BBC correspondent in South Asia from 1992 to 2004, based first in Pakistan then in India and finally in Kathmandu, Nepal.¬† From Islamabad, he covered the Afghan civil war in the 1990's and the rise of the Taliban.¬† He was in Kabul for three weeks after the Taliban took the city in September of 1996. In 1997, he was posted as BBC India reporter in New Delhi where he prepared reports and hosted television and radio specials around the 50th anniversary of the independence of India. While serving in New Delhi, Lak spent much of his time on the road in India, traveling from Kashmir to Kanyakumari, Gaumukh to Gujarat, reporting on environmental, political, social and economic issues.

In 2001, his reporting for BBC radio on the Gujarat earthquakes earned him a nomination for the One World broadcasting award for developmental journalism.¬† In that same year, Lak covered the massacre of the Nepalese royal family in Kathmandu and the aftermath of the Al Qaeda attacks on the United States in Pakistan, Afghanistan and India. During his time in Nepal, Lak also worked for the Economist, the Independent, the Sunday Independent, the Mail on Sunday (all UK), the South China Morning Post (Hong Kong) the Globe and Mail (Toronto) and is still a regular columnist in the Indian magazine, Outlook,¬† Since returning to North America, he has worked for the BBC, CBC and other media outlets on stories in Haiti, New Orleans after Hurricane Katrina, Mexico, the Caribbean and Washington D.C.

He is the author of <em>Mantras of Changes: Reporting India in Times of Flux, </em>and the recently published <em>India</em><em> Express: The Future of a New Superpower</em>.¬† He was the writer and director of Afghanistan, Journey through a broken country, Ichannel Toronto, ARTE France and MDF Germany. He is at work on a book about the Indian Diaspora and a novel about Nepal. Between books and films, Lak works as a political risk and media consultant on South Asia. Clients include the Committee to Protect Journalists and the Campaign for Tobacco-Free Kids.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:10:"Daniel Lak";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:10:"daniel-lak";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:59:05";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:59:05";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=339";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:60;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"508";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 13:48:38";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 13:48:38";s:12:"post_content";s:2937:"<div>Once a professional magician, Daniel Stashower wears hats both as a narrative historian and as a novelist with remarkable distinction. He is a two-time recipient of the prestigious Edgar Award from the Mystery Writers of America: for <em>Teller of Tales</em>‚Äîhis biography of Sherlock Holmes creator Arthur Conan Doyle‚Äîand for his editing of <em>Arthur Conan Doyle: A Life in Letters</em> with frequent collaborator Jon Lellenberg. Stashower‚Äôs work on Conan Doyle has also secured him the Anthony Award for Best Critical Work and two Agatha Awards for Best Nonfiction, from the Bouchercon World Mystery Convention and Malice Domestic.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Stashower‚Äôs forthcoming narrative history, <em>The Hour of Peril: The Secret Plot to Murder Lincoln Before the Civil War</em>, will be published by Minotaur Books in January 2013 and draws on the author‚Äôs lifelong interest in crime history and crime fiction to tell the true story of an 1861 assassination attempt on Abraham Lincoln‚Äîand the life of the man assigned to the case: America‚Äôs first ‚Äúprivate eye‚Äù Allan Pinkerton.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Daniel Stashower‚Äôs previous nonfiction books include <em>The Beautiful Cigar Girl: Mary Rogers, Edgar Allan Poe and the Invention of Murder</em> and <em>The Boy Genius and the Mogul: The Untold Story of Television</em>. He is also the author of five mystery novels featuring Harry Houdini as a detective, Sherlock Holmes, and an original magician detective based on Stashower‚Äôs own performing experience. A recipient of the Raymond Chandler Fulbright Fellowship in Detective and Crime Fiction Writing, Stashower has served as a Visiting Fellow at Oxford‚Äôs Wadham College. His writing has also appeared in <em>The New York Times</em>, <em>The Washington Post</em>, <em>AARP: The Magazine</em>, <em>National Geographic Traveller</em>, and <em>Smithsonian</em> magazine.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Born in Cleveland, Stashower received a BA from Northwestern University and an MFA from Columbia University. He has been a contributing editor for Time-Life Books on series such as <em>The Civil War</em> and <em>Mysteries of the Unknown</em>, is a member of the Society of American Magicians, and has been a member of the Society of Psychical Research. He is also a member of the most famous Sherlockian society, the Baker Street Irregulars, whose invitation-only ranks have included Isaac Asimov and Neil Gaiman.</div>
<div></div>
<div>An inveterate performer, Stashower has given hundreds of talks including large-scale appearances at the Library of Congress and the Smithsonian, and college appearances at Harvard and Oxford. He has performed at the historic Players Club in New York City and for Mensa, the high IQ society, and once appeared on a panel at the Anthony Boucher Memorial World Mystery Convention as Houdini, attired in straitjacket. He lives with his wife in Bethesda, Maryland.</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:16:"Daniel Stashower";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:16:"daniel-stashower";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-29 16:08:14";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-29 20:08:14";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=508";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:61;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"458";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 04:33:27";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 04:33:27";s:12:"post_content";s:1340:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>
<div>

After helping thousands of students find and get into colleges that truly matched their interests, Danny wrote his book, <em>The Ultimate College Acceptance System</em>, which was published in July, 2006 by St. Martin's Press.

Danny Ruderman started his parent company, Admit U Inc., in 1997 as a tutoring, test preparation and college admission counseling enterprise. He also travels the country speaking to families at different schools, companies, and PTA events.

Danny graduated with Honors from Stanford University and holds a BA in Human Biology with an emphasis in Education. In 1996, he was named a Merit Teacher for his work at Campbell Hall School in Los Angeles. Danny has worked as an educational therapist for K&amp;M Associates in Los Angeles and as a standardized test instructor for Ivy West. He is also a member of the Western Association of College Admissions Counselors (WACAC). He has been featured on a variety of television and radio programs, as well as in periodicals such as¬†NPR's Marketplace,¬†Fox News,¬†The Los Angeles Times, Barry Kibrick's¬†Between the Lines¬†on PBS,¬†College Bound Magazine,¬†The¬†Bill Handel Show, and¬†Powernomics. Danny is also a regular contributor to¬†Money 101¬†on KNX 1070 in Los Angeles.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Danny Ruderman";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"danny-ruderman";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-19 17:22:04";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-19 21:22:04";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=458";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:62;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"959";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-05-01 18:35:35";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-01 18:35:35";s:12:"post_content";s:2829:"Darrell Ezell is a professor, author, and cross-cultural relations specialist with expertise in managing global change. His interdisciplinary research is accentuated in his inaugural book, <i>Beyond Cairo: US Engagement with the Muslim World.</i>

&nbsp;

As a part of Palgrave Macmillan‚Äôs Global Public Diplomacy Book Series, this book examines the U.S.‚Äôs once enthusiastic commitment to restore trusted relations with the Arab and larger Muslim world since President Barack Obama‚Äôs 2009 ‚ÄúNew Beginning‚Äù address in Cairo, Egypt.¬† This book tackles the problem with public diplomacy as the U.S. has been practicing it and provides a roadmap for the White House and State Department to re-engage the Muslim world over the coming years.

&nbsp;

As an expert in cross-cultural relations, Ezell writes widely on issues related to the Middle East and North African, human rights, ethnic conflict, and pop culture.¬† His human rights activism is featured in the John Fiege film, <i>Mississippi Chicken</i>, highlighting his advocacy for fair treatment of Latino poultry workers in rural Mississippi.

&nbsp;

Known by many as a captivating young man with an infectious gift to warm the core of any stranger, Ezell is inspired to participate in causes that build upon a legacy deriving from his family‚Äôs involvement in the Alabama Civil Rights Movement. In order to accomplish that successfully and unapologetically, he made his way to New York after 9/11 to study conflict resolution, pursuing a M.A. in Theology and Social Ethics at Union Theological Seminary and Columbia University.¬† There he demonstrated his commitment to building bridges between religious and political leaders, first by working closely in Jewish, Christian, and Muslim communities in post-9/11 New York City with the Interfaith Center of New York and later in Chicago, IL at Interfaith Worker Justice.

&nbsp;

Garnering international attention while completing his Ph.D. in England, Ezell worked at the U.S. Department of State and the William J. Clinton Foundation (Clinton School of Public Service).

&nbsp;

He has been invited as a consultant to non-government organizations, think-tanks and universities on how best to manage global change. His sense of humor, knowledge, confidence, and passion combined make him captivating to media and live audiences alike. Ezell‚Äôs achievements in the United States and Europe have provided him a global platform as a dynamic speaker to deliver keynote addresses for international organizations, panel and workshop discussions at conferences, and lectures for academic institutions.

&nbsp;

Ezell holds a Ph.D. from the University of Birmingham in England, and currently lives in Louisiana, teaching international relations at Tulane University and Louisiana State University.";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Darrell Ezell";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"darrell-ezell";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-01 18:35:35";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-01 18:35:35";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://www.macmillanspeakers.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=959";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:63;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"129";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-12 22:12:35";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-12 22:12:35";s:12:"post_content";s:1852:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
