David Kirby is author of the critically acclaimed book <em>Evidence of Harm, Mercury in Vaccines and the Autism Epidemic: A Medical Controversy</em>, which debuted¬† on The New York Times bestseller list and is still widely read today. A professional journalist for over 15 years,¬†Kirby has appeared on such venues as Meet the Press, Larry King Live, The Today Show, Imus in the Morning, CNN, Montel Williams, Air America, and many others.

Kirby, whose next book is about Factory Farming, is a regular contributor to the Huffington Post, has been a professional journalist for over 15 years, including extensive contributions to The New York Times<em>.</em> He was a foreign correspondent in Mexico and Central America from 1986-1990. Kirby has also worked in politics, medical research and public relations.¬†He lives in Brooklyn, NY.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:11:"David Kirby";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:11:"david-kirby";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-20 09:51:17";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-20 13:51:17";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=328";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:69;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"337";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:56:06";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:56:06";s:12:"post_content";s:779:"David Paul Kuhn is an expert analyst of presidential and gender politics. He is the author of <em>The Neglected Voter: White Men and the Democratic Dilemma.</em> James Carville called it a "must read for Democrats who want to win" and General Wes Clark called it ‚ÄúA brilliantly insightful analysis of American politics at the national level.‚Äù Kuhn specializes in the male side of the gender gap. He covered the 2008 presidential election as a Senior Political Writer for the conversation-driver Politico.com and covered the 2004 presidential campaign as Chief Political Writer for CBS News. He has also written for publications from<em> </em>The Washington Post Magazine to The Wall Street Journal, and has appeared as a frequent commentator on news networks from BBC to CNN.";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"David Paul Kuhn";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"david-paul-kuhn";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-20 09:52:56";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-20 13:52:56";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=337";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:70;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"425";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 03:55:23";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 03:55:23";s:12:"post_content";s:1164:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
