HARRY CARSON is a lecturer and motivational speaker to groups that range from juvenile and prison inmates to high school scholars, from college athletes to corporate executives and political leaders.

Carson‚Äôs 13-year stint with the New York Football Giants is one of the longest tenures in club history. The indestructible former linebacker served as Team Captain for 10 of his 13 seasons.¬†Rated the #1 ‚ÄúInside Linebacker‚Äù in NFL history according to <em>Pro Football Weekly</em>, Carson was named to the All-Rookie Team after his first NFL season. He once made an amazing 25 tackles in a Monday Night Football Game against the Green Bay Packers.

Currently Carson serves as Executive Director of the Fritz Pollard Alliance, an organization representing National Football League minority non-player personnel dedicated to creating greater racial diversity within the National Football League.

Carson is President of Harry Carson Inc. a Sports Consulting and Promotions Company. HCI consults with media outlets, educational sources and corporations on sports as well as non-sports related issues. Harry Carson Inc. provides expert television, radio, print media and internet commentary on sports matters.

He is affiliated with many organizations and involved with numerous charities.¬†He has served as an Advisor to the Congress of Neurological Surgeons and is a member of the Brain Injury Association‚Äôs Sports Injury Prevention Council. Former Governor Christine Whitman appointed Mr. Carson as a member of the New Jersey Advisory Council on Traumatic Brain Injury.¬†He has established himself as an authority and internationally recognized speaker on Concussions in Sports.¬†His two books, <em>Point of Attack</em> (1985) and <em>Captain for Life</em> (2011), highlight his personal experiences with concussions and other injuries from playing the game of football.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Harry Carson";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"harry-carson";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-29 10:20:47";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-29 14:20:47";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=178";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:104;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"131";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-12 22:16:23";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-12 22:16:23";s:12:"post_content";s:2297:"Heather Bauer is a nationally recognized nutrition expert, author, and founder of Nu-Train, a New York City-based diet and nutrition counseling center. Over the last decade Heather has taught thousands of people how to safely lose weight and keep it off for good. Her success stories range from those working long hours on Wall Street, to doctors, lawyers, mothers, athletes and celebrities.In 2008 Heather released her first book, <em>The Wall Street Diet</em>, a program designed especially for busy people that don‚Äôt have time to diet. In Heather‚Äôs second book, <em>Bread Is the Devil </em>(due out in January 2012), she provides time-tested strategies and a 21-day plan to help readers overcome common diet pitfalls, what Bauer refers to as "Diet Devils". Some of these Devils include "The Late Night Shuffle (for those midnight marauders that just can‚Äôt stay out of the kitchen), "Road Hogging" (for travelers who decide to put their healthy habits on hold when on the road) and "The Plunge" (for anyone that wonders where that whole sleeve of cookies went).Heather founded Nu-Train (short for Nutrition Training) in 2001 on the premise that in order to be successful and sustainable, a weight loss program must work with ones existing habits, not against them.¬†As such, Nu-Train‚Äôs program goes beyond traditional nutrition science taking into account critical and often overlooked factors such as lifestyle, taste, preferences and diet history.Heather sits on <em>Cooking Light</em> magazine‚Äôs Nutrition Advisory Board and has appeared on popular TV and Radio shows such as CBS-TV‚Äôs <em>The Early Show</em>, CNN, <em>The Tyra Banks Show</em>, FOX Morning News, and Martha Stewart Living Radio on SiriusXM.¬† She has also been a featured nutritionist in <em>The New York Times</em>, <em>The Wall Street Journal</em>, <em>Self</em> magazine, <em>In Touch Weekly</em>, <em>InStyle</em>,<em> Shape</em>, <em>Gotham</em> magazine and <em>Ladies‚Äô Home Journal</em>.Heather received her BS and RD from the University of Wisconsin and is a member of the American Dietetic Association (ADA) and the New York State Dietetic Association (NYSDA).¬†She lives in Connecticut with her husband, daughter and twin boys. When she‚Äôs not chasing after her children, she‚Äôs usually out running.";s:10:"post_title";s:22:"Heather Bauer, RD, CDN";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:20:"heather-bauer-rd-cdn";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-20 15:19:33";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-20 19:19:33";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=131";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:105;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"992";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-05-06 13:36:05";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-06 13:36:05";s:12:"post_content";s:2059:"One of the newest cast members of BravoTV‚Äôs hit show, <i>Real Housewives of New York City</i>, Heather Thomson is the woman behind the successful <i>Yummie by Heather Thomson</i> brand. She singlehandedly transformed the global perception of shapewear and is responsible for revolutionizing the industry by making it comfortable and sexy. As a working mother of two, Thomson‚Äôs personal desire to shed her excess baby weight fueled the inspiration behind <i>Yummie by Heather Thomson</i>, and is now truly a lifestyle brand meeting women‚Äôs everyday shaping needs.

&nbsp;

Her work is backed by her 15 years as a successful designer and stylist who has worked with some of the biggest names in the entertainment industry. Thomson was the founding Design Director for Sean ‚ÄúDiddy‚Äù Combs‚Äô line and has worked alongside superstars Beyonc√© Knowles and Jennifer Lopez in creating and launching their respective labels, ‚ÄúSweetface,‚Äù ‚ÄúHouse of Der√©on,‚Äù and ‚ÄúMiss Tina.‚Äù She has also been credited as the major force behind multiple CFDA award nominations and gained recognition for one of the most successful men‚Äôs apparel launches ever.

&nbsp;

In addition to her work in the fashion industry as the Founder and Chief Creative Officer of <i>Yummie by Heather Thomson</i>, Thomson is a valued advocate for multiple philanthropic organizations ‚Äì she is a Celebrity Campaigner for organ donation and is heavily involved in supporting the public education efforts of the New York Organ Donor Network. Additionally, as a board member of the Kellner Pediatric Liver Foundation, Thomson raises funds and awareness to reduce the occurrence of pediatric liver disease having personally experienced the impact of these advocacies with her son.

&nbsp;

In 2010, Thomson was honored with a Spirit of Life Award recognizing her tireless efforts to promote power and self-confidence in women of all ages, and more recently, was honored as the <i>Liver Champion Award Recipient</i> from the American Liver Foundation this past September.";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"Heather Thomson";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"heather-thomson";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-21 15:39:09";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-21 19:39:09";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://www.macmillanspeakers.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=992";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:106;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1126";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-06-20 09:48:21";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-20 13:48:21";s:12:"post_content";s:2093:"Helen Wan is Associate General Counsel at the Time Inc. division of Time Warner, where she advises the Lifestyle portfolio of brands and Time Home Entertainment Inc. Before that, she practiced corporate law and entertainment law at firms in New York City. Wan is Co-Chair of Time Inc.‚Äôs Asian Pacific American Affinity Group and a frequent public speaker on advancing diversity in the legal profession, success strategies for women and minorities in the corporate workplace, and balancing career with other creative pursuits. She has spoken at law firms, law schools, colleges and universities, bar association conferences and professional networking events, and to corporate Diversity &amp; Inclusion teams.

&nbsp;

Wan‚Äôs first novel, <i>The Partner Track, </i>about a young Chinese-American woman up for partner at a prestigious global law firm, and about how outsider status and politics complicate her ascent up the corporate ladder, will be published by St. Martin‚Äôs Press in September 2013. <i>The Partner Track</i> has ben selected by Amherst College to be its ‚ÄúAmherst Reads‚Äù Book Selection for November 2013.

&nbsp;

Wan‚Äôs essays and reviews of fiction have been published in <i>The Washington Post</i> and elsewhere. Born in California and raised near Washington, D.C., she is a graduate of Amherst College and the University of Virginia School of Law. She lives in New York with her husband and young son.
