<div>
<div>In his hotly anticipated¬†new book, <em>Inside the Mind of Casey Anthony, </em>Dr. Keith Ablow delivers an objective psychological analysis that takes us through this modern day mystery. America‚Äôs most well-known forensic psychiatrist, Keith Ablow, M.D. has been retained to testify in some of the nation‚Äôs most highly publicized murder cases, and has evaluated and treated murderers, gang members and sexual offenders for the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, in addition tothousands of patients across the United States, in Europe and in Asia, including CEOs, elected officials, professional sports figures and world-renowned artists.</div>
He is the author of¬†many books, including <em>Inside the Mind of Casey Anthony, </em>the <em>New York Times </em>true crime bestseller <em>Inside the Mind of Scott Peterson</em><em>; the New York Times </em><em>self-help bestseller </em><em>The 7: Seven Wonders that Will Change Your Life</em> (co-written with Glenn Beck); and <em>Without Mercy: The Shocking True Story of a Doctor Who Murdered</em>, about a California doctor who killed one of Ablow‚Äôs good friends. His six novels, which feature a forensic psychiatrist who solves mysteries beyond the grasp of other investigators, have sold millions of copies around the world.

Dr. Ablow serves as psychiatry contributor to Fox News, contributing editor for <em>Good Housekeeping</em> and <em>Men‚Äôs Fitness</em>, and has made regular appearances on <em>Oprah</em> as well as frequent guest appearances on Court TV, the <em>Today </em>show, <em>Good Morning America, Larry King Live, The O‚ÄôReilly Factor with Bill O‚ÄôReilly, </em><em>Charlie Rose</em>, MSNBC, <em>Tyra, Montel</em> and a host of other television programs. His essays on human emotion and behavior have been published by <em>The New York Times, The Washington Post, USA Today, Discover, U.S. News and World Report, Good Housekeeping, Cosmopolitan, The Annals of Internal Medicine</em> and many other national publications. He has also been a reporter for <em>Newsweek</em>, medical editor and producer for Lifetime Medical Television in New York and Los Angeles and the Host and Executive Producer of the <em>Dr. Keith Ablow Show.</em>

Dr. Ablow is a much-sought-after public speaker and has addressed hospitals, corporations, professional organizations, private colleges and public schools. In addition to his fascinating forensic psychological insight into Casey Anthony, her parents, and the family dynamic that led to this year‚Äôs shocking case in Florida, Dr. Ablow delivers the inspiring message that we can take control of our lives by defeating the emotional and behavioral patterns that limit them. Dr. Ablow‚Äôs belief that people needlessly bury painful truths that, faced honestly, can turn into freeing insights and clear strategies for growth and success, has elicited a dramatic and transformative response from his live audiences.

Dr. Ablow received his medical degree from the Johns Hopkins School of Medicine, after graduating from Brown University. He is on the faculty of New England Medical Center in Boston and lives in the Boston area.

</div>
</div>
</div>
