Kristin was born in September 1960 in Southern California and grew up at the beach, and moved to Washington State at the age of eight.

After working in a trendy advertising agency,¬†Kristin decided to go to law school.¬†When she¬†was in my third-and final-year of law school and¬†her mother was in the hospital, facing the end of her long battle with cancer.¬†For the next few months, Kristin and her mother collaborated on the worst, most clich√©d historical romance ever written.

After¬†after her¬†death, Kristin packed up all those bits and pieces of paper they had collected and put them in a box in the back of my closet.¬†She got married and continued practicing law.

She then¬†found out¬†she was pregnant,¬†and was¬†on bed rest for five months. Her husband reminded¬†her of the book¬†she¬†had¬†started with¬†her mom. She pulled out the boxes of research material, dusted them off and began writing. By the time her son was born,¬†she had¬†finished a first draft and found an obsession.

Now, Kristin is a major bestselling novelist.¬† She continues to live in the Washington state with her family.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Kristin Hannah";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"kristin-hannah";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-26 11:34:11";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-26 15:34:11";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=281";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:159;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"174";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 14:17:28";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 14:17:28";s:12:"post_content";s:435:"LADY COLIN CAMPBELL, who is connected to the royal family through mutual ancestors and marriage, is the author of the <em>New York Times </em>bestseller <em>Diana in Private--</em>which was the first¬†book to reveal the¬†truth behind the "fairytale" marriage of the Prince and Princess of Wales--as well as <em>The Royal Marriages: What Really Goes on in the Private World of the Queen and Her Family, </em>and <em>The Real Diana.</em>";s:10:"post_title";s:19:"Lady Colin Campbell";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:19:"lady-colin-campbell";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-26 11:36:42";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-26 15:36:42";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=174";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:160;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"335";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:52:42";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:52:42";s:12:"post_content";s:2174:"LARRY KRAMER is a distinguished American playwright and¬†LGBT rights activist<em>. </em>He has won an Oscar nomination, two Obie Awards, the American Academy of Arts Award in Literature, and is a Pulitzer Award finalist.¬† As one of the most dynamic and influential forces for political activism, gay rights, public health policy, and AIDS-awareness, Larry is a widely-recognizable and remarkable speaker on these crucial issues.

&nbsp;

Larry is renowned for both his literary achievements and political activism. At the root of both is his life-long commitment to criticizing and correcting gay apathy and government and social indifference to AIDS. He is a founder of Gay Men‚Äôs Health Crisis, an AIDS service organization, and ACT UP, a widely effective direct action AIDS advocacy group. Larry‚Äôs most acclaimed plays include <em>The Normal Heart</em> (1985) and the Pulitzer Prize-finalist <em>The Destiny of Me</em> (1992). His screenplay for <em>Women in Love</em> was nominated for an Academy Award in 1969. He is also well-known for his influential novel <em>Faggots</em> (1978), a confrontational portrayal of gay culture, and his critical essay about the AIDS crisis, ‚Äú1,112 and Counting‚Äù (1983).

&nbsp;

Larry has also written the plays <em>Sissie‚Äôs Scrapbook</em>, <em>A Minor Dark Age</em>, and <em>Just Say No, A Play about Farce</em>. His other books are <em>The Tragedy of Today‚Äôs Gays</em> and <em>Reports From the Holocaust: The Story of an AIDS Activist</em>.

&nbsp;

The recent Broadway revival of <em>The Normal Heart</em> was nominated for five Tonys and won three, including Best Play. The forthcoming film version of <em>The Normal Heart</em> will star Mark Ruffalo and Julia Roberts. A revival of <em>The Destiny of Me</em> will be directed by Joe Mantello. And <em>The Normal Heart</em> will begin its cross country tour shortly.

&nbsp;

Larry earned his B.A. in English from Yale University. For the past three decades he has been researching American history and the cause of AIDS/HIVS for his novel The American People‚Äîit is due to be published in two volumes in 2013. He lives in New York City and Connecticut.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Larry Kramer";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"larry-kramer";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-28 16:30:12";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-28 20:30:12";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=335";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:161;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:2:"93";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-12 20:08:15";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-12 20:08:15";s:12:"post_content";s:957:"Laura Adams is a personal finance expert and author of the award-winning book <em>Money Girl‚Äôs Smart Moves to Grow Rich</em>. She hosts the top-rated Money Girl podcast on iTunes and QuickandDirtyTips.com with over 36 million downloads.Laura is a frequent personal finance contributor on FOX News, FOX Business, and <em>The Huffington Post</em>. Her advice has been featured on NBC News, in <em>USA Today</em>, <em>U.S. News and World Report</em>, <em>Time</em>, <em>Consumer Reports</em>, and many other media outlets.Laura‚Äôs passion is making personal finance easy to understand. Millions of readers, podcast listeners, and students benefit from smart, friendly, and down-to-earth financial guidance. She is a web entrepreneur and former corporate trainer who is requested for keynote speeches, conferences, educational events, and corporate workshops. She graduated from The University of the South and received an MBA from the University of Florida.";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Laura D. Adams";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"laura-d-adams";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-26 11:41:22";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-26 15:41:22";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:61:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=93";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:162;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"302";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 22:58:58";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 22:58:58";s:12:"post_content";s:1484:"<strong>Laurel House</strong>¬†is best known as QuickieChick, for¬†her popular YouTube videos providing fast and simple workouts and advice for everyday girls. She has written hundreds of articles as a lifestyle expert, that have appeared in national and online magazines including <em>Women‚Äôs Health</em>, <em>Men‚Äôs Journal</em>, <em>LA Daily News</em>, and more.

She has been an editor for <em>Fit </em>magazine, a "Fit Life Expert" for Exercise TV, and a regular contributor to Discovery‚Äôs Planet Green. Laurel has a QuickChick channel on Yahoo! Shine and is also the Career Expert on Campus Explorer. Her book,<em> QuickieChick‚Äôs Cheat Sheet to Life, Love, Food, Fitness, Fashion, and Finance on a Less Than Fabulous Budget </em>was published in May 2012. Laurel‚Äôs in-print expertise has led to over 100 television morning show appearances including: NBC‚Äôs <em>Weekend Today</em>, <em>Soap Talk</em>, <em>The Daily Buzz</em>, <em>Better</em> TV, Style Network‚Äôs <em>Modern Girl‚Äôs Guide to Life</em>, and <em>KTLA Morning News</em>, as well as CBS, Fox, and ABC Morning News shows both locally and nationally.

Well-known wellness and lifestyle companies have engaged her as their on-air spokesperson including Guthy-Renker, Microsoft, Tag Heuer watches, The Platinum Board, Hoover vacuums, TJ Maxx, KY Brand, M&amp;Ms, Norton, Dunkin‚Äô Donuts latte light, Progresso soup, Propel Water, Nature Made Vitamins, Danskin fitness clothes, and Olay beauty products.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Laurel House";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"laurel-house";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-26 11:59:34";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-26 15:59:34";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=302";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:163;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"117";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-12 21:33:20";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-12 21:33:20";s:12:"post_content";s:2668:"<div>Lauren Bacall is often considered the leading heroine of the film noir genre with a prolific career that spans over 50 years. Her on-screen beauty, as well as her trademark sultry voice, has made her an icon for several generations.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Bacall was born in 1924 as Betty Joan Perske, the only daughter of Jewish immigrants William Perske and Natalie Weinstein-Bacall, who divorced when Bacall was six years old.</div>
<div></div>
<div>As a teenager, Bacall was a part-time model and a movie usherette. The wife of legendary producer and director Howard Hawks‚Äô noticed Bacall modeling on the cover of Harper‚Äôs Bazaar, and urged her husband to call her for a screen test. She made her film debut at only 19 years old opposite Humphrey Bogart in ‚ÄúTo Have and Have Not.‚Äù</div>
<div></div>
<div>Bacall went on to marry Bogart in 1945, and starred with him in a second movie (also directed by Hawks), ‚ÄúThe Big Sleep.‚Äù Her character, the wealthy Vivian, showed powerful development of Bacall‚Äôs skills on screen. Her versatility as an actress was exemplified in her third film opposite Bogart, John Huston‚Äôs ‚ÄúKey Largo,‚Äù where she played a more vulnerable character.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Bacall often took time off between each film to spend time with her family, even during the peak of her career activity in the 50‚Äôs. During this decade, Bacall appeared in such films as ‚ÄúHow to Marry a Millionaire‚Äù (1953) and ‚ÄúWritten on the Wind‚Äù (1956). Bogart died in 1957, the same year Bacall starred in the sophisticated comedy, ‚ÄúDesigning Woman.‚Äù</div>
<div></div>
<div>In 1960, she married actor Jason Robard. She seldom appeared on screen in the 1960‚Äôs, opting to make a return to the stage (where she had made brief appearances as a teenager) instead. She ended her eight year hiatus in 1974 with her role in the movie, ‚ÄúMurder on the Orient Express.‚Äù</div>
<div></div>
<div>Throughout her career, Bacall has been presented with countless awards and honors, from a Tony Award in 1970 to the Bette Davis Medal of Honor in 2008. In 1997, Bacall received a Golden Globe for her role in ‚ÄúThe Mirror Has Two Faces.‚Äù The Stockholm Film Festival presented her with its Lifetime Achievement Award in 2000, and the American Film Institute named Bacall as one of its 50 Greatest American Screen Legends in 2005.</div>
<div></div>
Bacall has written two autobiographies, best-selling <em>Lauren Bacall: By Myself</em> (1978), which won a National Book Award in 1980, and <em>Now</em> (1994). She continues her career today, starring in award-winning movies such as Lars von Trier‚Äôs ‚ÄúDogville‚Äù (2003).";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Lauren Bacall";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"lauren-bacall";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2012-11-12 21:33:20";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-12 21:33:20";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=117";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:164;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"598";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-12-18 18:19:44";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-12-18 18:19:44";s:12:"post_content";s:1360:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>Leonard Zeskind is the author of <em>Blood and Politics: The History of White Nationalism from the Margins to the Mainstream</em>, published by Farrar Straus &amp; Giroux in 2009. He has written for The American Prospect, Rolling Stone, The Nation, The New York Times and the Los Angeles Times, among other publications in the United States.¬† He has also written book chapters and research monographs as well as for anti-racist publications in Germany and Sweden and for the British anti-fascist monthly Searchlight, published from London.</div>
<div></div>
<div>The John D. and Catherine T. MacArthur Foundation named him a Fellow in 1998 (one of its so-called ‚ÄúGenius Grants‚Äù). He has testified before a Parliamentary Subcommittee in the United Kingdom, given public lectures at universities in London and Berlin, and worked for three decades to curb the influence of racism, anti-Semitism and white supremacist groups in the United States.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Prior to 1982, he was a community activist and worked in industry for thirteen years: on an automobile assembly line, installing refrigerator motors in vending machines, and as a welder and first class fitter in steel fabrication plants.¬† He is president of the Institute for Research &amp; Education on Human Rights.</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"Leonard Zeskind";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"leonard-zeskind";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-26 14:13:56";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-26 18:13:56";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=598";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:165;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"527";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 14:14:35";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 14:14:35";s:12:"post_content";s:2266:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>
<div>

Leora Tanenbaum is the author of <em>Taking Back God: American Women Rising Up for Religious Equality.</em>¬† This book is about devout women‚ÄîCatholic, Protestant, Muslim, and Jewish‚Äîwho love their religion but are troubled about their second-class status within their faith and are doing something about it.¬†Her other books are <em>Catfight: Rivalries Among Women‚ÄîFrom Diets to Dating, From the Boardroom to the Delivery Room, </em>about the ways in which women often try to sabotage one another, and <em>Slut! Growing Up Female With a Bad Reputation</em>, about girls labeled "sluts" by their peers.¬† <em>Catfight </em>has been published in Germany, Australia/New Zealand, Turkey, Greece, and was a selection of the Quality Paperback Book Club in 2003.¬† <em>Slut! </em>has been published in Turkey and in¬†the United States it<em> </em>is a staple in women‚Äôs studies courses on college campuses.

In addition to books, Tanenbaum has written fo<em>r</em> Newsday, Seventeen, Cosmopolitan, Salon, The New York Observer, Ms., The Nation, The Women‚Äôs Review of Books, and many other newspapers and magazines.¬† She is currently a blogger for The Huffington Post<em>.</em> She is a member of the Editorial Advisory Board of the Feminist Press. Tanenbaum has been featured and profiled in Redbook, The Washington Post, and the Forward, among many other publications<em>.</em>¬† She lectures widely at venues including the Commonwealth Club in San Francisco, Makor at the 92nd Street Y in Manhattan, and campuses such as Stanford, Duke, Columbia, University of Michigan-Ann Arbor, and Spelman.

Tanenbaum regularly appears on TV news and entertainment shows as an expert on women‚Äôs issues.¬† She has appeared on Oprah, The Today Show, CBS This Morning, The O'Reilly Factor, Inside Edition, Politically Incorrect<em>,</em> and many other programs.¬† She is also a frequent guest on National Public Radio and VH1.¬† She has been featured in several documentaries and TV specials including <em>Sluts: The Documentary </em>(2006), which was broadcast on the Sundance Channel and the Independent Film Channel. She lives in New York City with her husband and two sons.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"Leora Tanenbaum";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"leora-tanenbaum";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2012-11-14 14:14:35";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 14:14:35";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=527";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:166;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"180";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 14:25:12";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 14:25:12";s:12:"post_content";s:1182:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>Senator Lincoln served the State of Rhode Island in the United States Senate from 1999-2007.¬† A graduate of Brown University, Chafee entered politics in 1985 as a delegate to the Rhode Island Constitutional Convention.¬† A year later, he was elected to the Warwick, Rhode Island City Council, where he served until his election as Warwick's mayor in 1992, a post he held until he was appointed to his father John Chafee's seat in the Senate upon his sudden death in 1999.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Serving as a Republican in the Senate, Chafee has long been a supporter of gay rights, environmental causes, and pro-choice policies.¬† He was also the only Republican in the Senate to vote against the use of force in Iraq.¬† Chafee eventually left the party to become an Independent, and during the 2008 presidential elections, Chafee was a high-profile supporter of¬†Barack Obama.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Chafee now serves as a Distinguished Visiting Fellow at Brown University, and on the advisory board of J Street, a pro-Israel lobbying group that promotes diplomatic relations between Israel and its neighbors.</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Lincoln Chafee";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"lincoln-chafee";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-26 14:24:02";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-26 18:24:02";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=180";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:167;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"325";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:37:26";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 23:37:26";s:12:"post_content";s:1890:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>
<div>

Washington journalist Linda Killian is the author of the upcoming book <em>The Swing Vote: The Untapped Power of Independents</em>‚Äîa forward-thinking examination of the independent centrist voters who will decide our next national election‚Äîas well as <em>The Freshmen: What Happened to the Republican Revolution?</em> which was praised as a ‚Äúfair, thoughtful, and eminently readable account‚Äù of the anti-Democratic 1994 election and the outcome of Republican control in the House of Representatives.<em> </em>

Killian is a columnist for Politico.com and the <em>U.S. News &amp; World Report</em> online, and has also written for a host of other publications including <em>The Washington Post</em>, <em>Los Angeles Times</em>, <em>People </em>magazine, <em>The New Republic</em>, <em>The Weekly Standard</em>, <em>The American Spectator</em>, <em>The Christian Science Monitor</em>, <em>Redbook</em>, and <em>Washingtonian </em>magazine. She is a former senior scholar at the non-partisan Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars.

In 2000, Killian created and launched the Boston University Washington Journalism Center, which provides students with the opportunity to spend time in DC, reporting on Congress and the federal government for the Boston University Washington news Service and other New England news organizations.

From 1993-1995 she served as the senior editor of National Public Radio‚Äôs <em>All Things Considered</em>, ¬†and was previously a reporter for <em>Forbes </em>magazine, United Press International, and several other major daily newspapers. She holds a master‚Äôs degree in public administration from Harvard University‚Äôs Kennedy School of Government and graduated cum laude from Boston University with degrees in journalism and political science.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"Linda Killian";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:13:"linda-killian";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-26 14:33:12";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-26 18:33:12";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=325";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:168;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"374";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:33:58";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-14 02:33:58";s:12:"post_content";s:2121:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
<div>Lisa B. Marshall is passionate about communication. She helps organizations and individuals to improve productivity through more effective, engaging and compelling communication. Marshall focuses on science, technology and business professionals such as MDs, DOs, DDSs, PhDs, PharmDs, Computer Scientists, MBAs, CPAs, CFPs, and JDs.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Lisa‚Äôs clients describe her and her programs this way: ‚ÄúVery practical and empowering.‚Äù ‚ÄúVery high-energy, entertaining, and content rich.‚Äù ‚ÄúEngaging, effective, informative, and fun.‚Äù ‚ÄúEnjoyed her sense of humor and real life examples.‚Äù ‚ÄúHer material is fresh (far from generic) and highly customized.‚Äù ‚ÄúShe is passionate and her enthusiasm resonates.‚Äù</div>
<div></div>
<div>Host and creator of "The Public Speaker" this fun, friendly, and practical Internet radio show reaches a worldwide audience with over 135,000 downloads each month. Lisa has been interviewed by USA Today, Regan Communications Group, The Scientist, Prevention Magazine and others. She holds a masters degree in interpersonal, organizational and intercultural communication.</div>
<div></div>
<div>She has spoken, trained and coached in the US, China, Malaysia, England, Germany and Spain. Her corporate clients include Genentech, Locus Pharmaceuticals, Merck &amp; Co., Ventana Medical Systems (Roche), and others. Her academic clients include University of Pennsylvania, Harvard University, Stanford University, John Hopkins Medicine, Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center and others.¬† Her association clients include American Heart Association, National Postdoc Association, ACM SIGCHI ‚Äì Computer-Human Interaction, Science Alliance-New York Academy of Sciences and others.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Lisa is fun and easy to work with.¬† She ensures a successful program with intensive pre-program research.¬† These activities can include sample submissions, participant interviews, surveys, and focus group discussions that allow her to create focused, client specific, unique programs.</div>
