Richard Torrenzano is chairman and chief executive of The Torrenzano Group, a strategic communications and high-stakes issues management firm specializing in building and protecting corporate reputations, enhancing shareholder value and helping clients grow their businesses.

The Torrenzano Group helps organizations take control of how they are perceived‚Ñ¢. For additional information visit: <a href="http://www.torrenzano.com/">www.torrenzano.com</a>

<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">New Book set for October 2011: </span></strong>The new book <em>Digital Assassination:</em> <em>Protecting your Reputation, Brand or Business Against Online Attacks, </em>authored by Richard Torrenzano and former White House speechwriter Mark Davis will be published by St. Martin‚Äôs Press in October 2011. Visit:¬† <a href="http://www.digitalassassinationbook.com/">www.digitalassassinationbook.com</a>

The book reveals how the Internet is used to¬†destroy¬†brands, reputations, even lives . . . and provides a course of actions to turn the table on digital assassins<em>.¬†</em>It is the preeminent work on Reputation Management in the Internet and digital age.

<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Background: </span></strong>Rich has counseled chief executives and boards of international corporations in the US, Europe, Latin America and Asia, as well as several heads of state. <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">¬†</span></strong>He has extensive hands on experience in the world‚Äôs financial markets.¬† Throughout a period of rapidly developing public policy issues, historic levels of market activity, unprecedented change in world affairs and intense media coverage, Rich planned and directed the New York Stock Exchange‚Äôs worldwide activities and programs.

For nearly a decade, he was a member of the Big Board‚Äôs management (policy) and executive (operations) committees.

<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Global Crisis Expert: </span></strong>A recognized global expert in crisis management, he managed the public strategies for significant global financial crises, including the market crash, October 1987, and the1998 Federal Reserve Bank‚Äôs $4 billion recapitalization of Long-Term Capital Management (LTCM), financed by a consortium of 14 of the world‚Äôs largest financial institutions.¬† His counsel and work helped restore confidence in the NYSE and U.S. capital markets.

Following the September 11th terrorist attacks, he provided counsel to top executives at Merrill Lynch, Lloyd‚Äôs of London, Nasdaq Stock Market, National Association of Securities Dealers, American Stock Exchange and Security Traders Association ‚Äì all significantly affected by the crisis.

Rich developed and implemented public strategies to deal with other significant market moments including insider trading scandals, corporate mergers, acquisitions and IPOs, corporate governance and shareholder activism issues, bankruptcies, regulatory and disciplinary actions, and digital trading.

<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">International Scope: </span></strong>At the request of the President of the United States ‚Äì following the Bush-Gorbachev Malta Summit - Rich was instrumental in negotiating and planning the landmark NYSE USSR-US Moscow seminar on financial markets.¬† It was attended by several hundred academic, business, financial, and government leaders in the Soviet Union.¬† The program served as a catalyst for the opening of new exchanges in Moscow and St. Petersburg.

He negotiated and planned the historic China-US symposium on financial markets in Beijing.¬† Those meetings with key government and business galvanized the opening of the stock exchange in Shanghai, moving China towards a new economic system. Concurrent with those activities, Rich coordinated White House-related activities for the NYSE chief executive officer - in his capacity as chairman of President Reagan‚Äôs Board of Advisors on Private Sector Initiatives.

<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Corporate Positions: </span></strong>Rich also served as director and senior vice president-corporate affairs and a member of the Executive Management Committee for SmithKline Beecham, Plc. SB, which was one of the world‚Äôs leading healthcare companies with more than 300 products marketed in 130 countries and revenues exceeding $14 billion. SB merged with Glico in 2000.

Richard Torrenzano is one of our most popular business¬†<a href="http://macmillanspeakers.com/"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">keynote speaker</span></a><span style="text-decoration: underline;">s</span>¬†and is also frequently scheduled as a¬†<a href="http://www.macmillanspeakers.com/topic/Communication"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">conference speaker on communications</span></a>.¬†See also our other¬†<a href="http://macmillanspeakers.com/"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">keynote and motivational speakers</span></a>¬†,¬†<a href="http://www.macmillanspeakers.com/topic/GlobalAffairs"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">global affairs experts</span></a>, and¬†<a href="http://macmillanspeakers.com/topic/PoliticsPundits"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">political pundits</span></a>.

</div>
</div>
</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:18:"Richard Torrenzano";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:18:"richard-torrenzano";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-06-27 10:16:23";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-06-27 14:16:23";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=538";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:210;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"248";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 16:29:25";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 16:29:25";s:12:"post_content";s:3141:"A contemporary Renaissance man, Richie Frieman is the host of the popular Modern Manners Guy podcast at QuickandDirtyTips.com. His humorous and distinct voice stems from his colorful career history: at only 33, Richie Frieman has seen almost everything to which manners can possibly apply‚Äîfrom a wild and unique career as a professional wrestler, to work as a children‚Äôs books writer and illustrator, a music columnist, inventor, and entrepreneur. Whether in the boardroom or in the wrestling ring, Frieman has experienced manners and etiquette at its best and at its most bizarre. As a result, Frieman‚Äôs outlook on modern manners is humorous, honest, and above all else, helpful. Having walked many miles in a number of different shoes, Frieman‚Äôs tales of etiquette dos and don‚Äôts span a broad category of topics.¬†He is founder and CEO of the award-winning music and lifestyle e-magazine, PensEyeView.com (PEV), which has featured nearly 1,000 consecutive interviews with a different artist every 48 hours‚Äîfrom emerging artists to Grammy Award winners‚Äîsince its inception three years ago. Frieman was awarded a Laureate medal (formerly known as the Smithsonian Award) for his work with PEV at the 2008 Computerworld Honors Program, after being nominated by the CEOs of Research In Motion, the creators of BlackBerry. Richie Frieman is also the author of two children‚Äôs books in his original "Terple the Turtle" series. "Terple ‚Äì The Sky is Just the Start" was named a finalist in the Indie Excellence Awards National Book Awards, and its follow-up, "Terple ‚Äì Always Dream Bigger," is the winner of the 2012 Gelett Burgess Children‚Äôs Book Award for Best Poetry and Rhyme book, and has also been awarded the Literary Classics Seal of Approval. With the two books as an avenue for charitable work, Frieman has done dozens of signings and readings for organizations such as the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation, Habitat for Humanity, Karma Dogs, Maryland Food Bank, The Ed Reed Foundation, the Mt. Washington Pediatric Hospital and the world renowned Kennedy Krieger Children‚Äôs Hospital. In addition to encouraging children to fulfill their dreams,¬†Frieman backs them by offering a portion of the profits from his book (for the life of it) to charity.

Frieman attended The University of Maryland College Park, graduating in 2001 with a degree in Fine Arts and a concentration in graphic design. Having shown work professionally in sculpture, painting and illustration, Frieman is also an active entrepreneur. In 2011, he launched the revolutionary garment accessory, Collar Keeps (<a href="http://www.collarkeeps.com">www.collarkeeps.com</a>), to help eliminate the flyaway collar on dress shirts. In 2012, he opened Charm City Babies, a vintage rock n' roll, pop-culture-inspired baby clothing line that donates a onesie to a child in need across the globe for each one sold through its online store. Along with his work in the arts, Frieman has been known as the professional wrestler "The Thrill From Israel" Buster Maccabi since 2000, having won more than a dozen titles in various federations throughout the country.";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Richie Frieman";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"richie-frieman";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2012-11-13 16:29:25";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 16:29:25";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=248";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:211;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"108";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-12 21:12:59";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-12 21:12:59";s:12:"post_content";s:3429:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
