Simon Tolkien is the author of the crime novel <em>Final Witness</em>.¬† He is the grandson of J.R.R. Tolkien, the author of The Lord of the Rings series. After his parents‚Äô divorce when he was five, he grew up with his mother, a sculptress, in a small village outside of Oxford. Tolkien attended the public Roman Catholic Downside School, where he was educated by Benedictine monks. At Oxford University, he studied Modern History at Trinity College.

&nbsp;

Since 1994, Tolkien has been a barrister in London specializing in serious crime. He has two children, Nicholas and Anna, with his wife Tracy.¬† They live in London and Southern California.

