Tamsen loves all things tech, fashion and green. She can be seen bright and early Monday-Friday hosting the WPIX-TV, Morning News starting at 4AM.
In January 2010, Tamsen made her Broadway debut in CHICAGO, the musical, and appeared¬† in Broadway‚Äôs IN THE HEIGHTS, followed by on-stage debuts in Broadway‚Äôs IN THE HEIGHTS and ROCK OF AGES.
Along with her job as a media personality, Tamsen works alongside, Matt Titus, a TV Host and nationally renowned relationship expert.¬† The two co-authored the book Why Hasn‚Äôt He Called? How Guys Really Think and How to Get the Right One Interested in You, their second book, Why Hasn‚Äôt He Proposed? Go From The First Date To Setting The Date and their most recent, Don‚Äôt Date Dumb.
Tamsen has appeared on The Today Show, Good Morning America, The CBS Early Show, Tyra Banks and The Nate Berkus Show just to name a few.";s:10:"post_title";s:12:"Tamsen Fadal";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:12:"tamsen-fadal";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2012-11-13 15:39:40";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 15:39:40";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://localhost/macmillian_site/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=226";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:245;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"917";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"3";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-04-29 15:06:02";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-04-29 15:06:02";s:12:"post_content";s:2707:"Tana Amen, BSN, RN, is a nurse, health and fitness expert, and nationally-renowned speaker. She is also a nutrition consultant and coach for the popular Daniel Plan, the inspirational health movement led by Pastor Rick Warren, and including Dr. Daniel Amen, Dr. Mark Hyman, and Dr. Mehmet Oz. Followers of The Daniel Plan lost more than 125 tons in 2011.

Working alongside her husband, <i>New York Times </i>bestselling author and physician, Daniel Amen, MD, Tana offers nutritional guidance and practical support to hundreds of thousands of Amen followers. Her book, <i>The Omni Diet</i>, is the culmination of her decade-long quest to study relationship between food and the body, and to understand how proper nutrition not only impacts weight loss, but actually holds the key to reversing chronic disease, decreasing inflammation, healing the body, and dramatically improving quality of life.

By the time she had reached her mid-30s, Tana Amen had nearly given up on good health. Through a lifetime of chronic medical ailments, including severe digestive issues, recurrent infections and, most devastatingly, a battle with thyroid cancer, there was never a point when Tana felt consistently healthy. Doctors ascribed her poor health to genetics, bad luck, and a family history of obesity and heart disease‚Äîbut even when Tana committed to a standard fitness and eating regimen, her health failed to improve. That‚Äôs when she realized that she needed to figure out how to improve her health . . . for good.

Tana‚Äôs fresh approach, her energetic presence, her enthusiastic style, and her ability to connect personally and directly with people‚Äîeven in large groups‚Äîhave made her an in-demand speaker. Tana has given dozens of presentations at the Saddleback Church, Superhero You, High Performance Brains, Women‚Äôs Wellness, the Institute for the Advancement of Human Behavior, the Omega Institute, Beacon House, Salvation Army Adult Rehabilitation Center, The Want Institute, and other wellness-focused organizations.

She shares healthy eating tips in her newsletter and blog on <a href="http://www.tanaamen.com/">www.TanaAmen.com</a>, <i>The Huffington Post</i>, and Livestrong.com. She is also a coach on The Amen Solution online community and answers questions via her blog on <a href="http://www.amenclinics.com/">www.AmenClinics.com</a>.

Tana has played an important part in Dr. Amen‚Äôs astonishingly successful PBS specials, which have raised more than $45 million for public television and have made Daniel Amen one of the country‚Äôs most respected doctors. She is a busy mother and nutrition leader of the Amen household, as well as an accomplished martial arts enthusiast.";s:10:"post_title";s:9:"Tana Amen";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:9:"tana-amen";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-05-28 15:35:38";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-05-28 19:35:38";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:62:"http://www.macmillanspeakers.com/?post_type=speaker&#038;p=917";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:7:"speaker";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:246;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"204";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"4";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2012-11-13 15:03:46";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2012-11-13 15:03:46";s:12:"post_content";s:1674:"<div id="ctl00_cphMainContent_divSpeakerDesc">
