Terra Wellington has been a popular television guest on such programs as The Montel Williams Show and WCBS This Morning due to her expertise in wellness and lifestyle topics.¬†A Second City-trained actress and improv artist, Terra is the former wellness editor of Fit Body and Real, and she has been a major-brand spokesperson for over 50¬†companies, including Procter &amp; Gamble, Nestle, Clorox, Hormel Foods, Campbell Soup Company, and Disney.

Her new book<em> The Mom's Guide to Growing Your Family Green: Saving the Earth Begins at Home</em> is a comprehensive real-mom's guide on how to help the planet and protect your family.¬† On her blog MomsAndThePlanet.com, she covers information about healthy living and the environment.¬† She is also a contributor to ClubMom.com and Aisle7 (formerly Healthnotes) and wrote the syndicated column Terra Wellington‚Äôs Balanced Living. A supporter of homeopathy and ocean conservation,¬†Terra currently resides in the Los Angeles area with her husband and three children.

